Since the process completed all prior steps successfully, it is suggested that the process IS NOT RESTARTED FROM THE TOP.
This session should have removed the trigger file $PMSourceFileDir/$$BLD_TRG_FLE_NME_WKLT.trg - if it did not complete this, do it manually.
This session should have triggered an email to the client (next email task in wf). If that did not run, send the information to the DL manually.
If the RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD was NOT updated to 'C', do that update manually WHERE RPT_PRCS_NB = $$RPT_PRCS_NB_WKLT.

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Text
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
An error occurred in the workflow %w running in %d.
Please check the workflow log to determine which session failed.
If this RPT_PRCS_NB is to be rerun, after fixing the error this workflow can only be rerun after the MVS $$MVS_DB2_OWNER_WF.KSZ6020_RPT_PRCS_CNTL.RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD is set to 'R1' WHERE RPT_PRCS_NB = $$RPT_PRCS_NB_WF.
If the issue is not going to be fixed and this specific RPT_PRCS_NB will not be rerun for this workflow, then the RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD MUST be set to 'F'. Otherwise no other RPT_PRCS_NB will ever be run for this client until the current RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD of 'F2' is changed.
